This paper discusses the impact of population size on the performance of evolutionary algorithms, which is a topic closely related to the field of neural networks and artificial intelligence (cs.NE and cs.AI). The paper also presents a theoretical analysis of the problem, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the role of population diversity, which is a concept commonly used in data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper analyzes the conditions under which large populations can be harmful, which is relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY).
